@startuml
title POST /api/v1/enrollments — Error Paths
autonumber

actor Client
participant "join_course\n_with_code()" as View
participant "IsAuthenticated" as Auth
participant "primary_role()" as RoleCheck
participant "redeem_student\n_join_course()" as Redeem
database Postgres

== Error: Not a student (403) ==
Client -> View: POST /enrollments {code}\n[JWT: teacher user]
View -> Auth: check JWT
Auth --> View: authenticated
View -> RoleCheck: primary_role(user)
RoleCheck --> View: "TEACHER"
View --x Client: 403 "Only student accounts\ncan redeem student codes"

== Error: Invalid code (400) ==
Client -> View: POST /enrollments\n{code: "INVALID"}\n[JWT: student user]
View -> Auth: check JWT
Auth --> View: authenticated
View -> RoleCheck: primary_role(user)
RoleCheck --> View: "STUDENT"
View -> Redeem: redeem_student_join_course(user, code)
Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT registration_codes\nWHERE code_hash = ? FOR UPDATE
Postgres --> Redeem: NULL (not found)
Redeem --x View: ValueError("Invalid or expired code")
View --x Client: 400 "Invalid or expired code"

== Error: Already enrolled (201 but flagged) ==
Client -> View: POST /enrollments {code}\n[JWT: student, already in course]
View -> Redeem: redeem_student_join_course(user, code)
Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT registration_codes\nFOR UPDATE
Postgres --> Redeem: valid code
Redeem -> Postgres: SELECT enrollments\nWHERE course + student
Postgres --> Redeem: Enrollment (exists!)
note over Redeem: already_enrolled = True\nNO code usage increment
Redeem --> View: (Enrollment, already=True)
View --> Client: 201 Created\n{message: "Already enrolled",\nalreadyEnrolled: true}
@enduml
